# Composition reference — MEX vs KOR full time

**Source image:** `design-tokens/reference/compositions/MEX-KOR-fulltime.png`  
(Figma Section E export at 1920×1080 — static poster, no motion.)

Read this file + the PNG before changing placement, draw order, overlap, or zone logic.

---

## Canvas structure

| Region | Rule |
|--------|------|
| Background | Flat warm paper (`paper/background`) — no gradient |
| Center | Empty vertical gutter (~12% artwork width). **Nothing** crosses it |
| Header | "World Cup" centered, top band |
| Footer | `{Home} VS {Away}` large centered above waveform; venue · date below |
| Left zone | Mexico (MEX palette) — all home marks stay here |
| Right zone | South Korea (KOR palette) — all away marks stay here |

---

## Per-side cluster anatomy (back → front)

Each team side is one **dense collage**, not a scattered field. Build in this draw order:

1. **Goal** — largest vertical jagged panel; acts as a **backdrop anchor** inside the zone (MEX: green body + orange accent spike; KOR: burgundy/lavender body + lighter accent). Goals are tall relative to other marks (several× shot size).
2. **Foul** — black ink fracture marks (`ink.mark` only); flame-like, vertical; overlap goals and mid-layer marks.
3. **PossessionGrid** — 10×10 circle grid in the **corner only** (see below); sits above goal plane visually in the reference.
4. **Shot** — pixelated diamond squares (`c1` + `c2`); orthogonal (0° or 90° only); medium size; overlap freely.
5. **Offside** — stacked wave bars (`c3`); often read as vertical “S” stacks in the reference; orthogonal.
6. **Corner** — pinwheel (`c2`); orthogonal.
7. **ShotOnTarget** — bold starburst (`c2`); larger than shots; centered on placement point.
8. **Cards** — small rectangles + ink detail; yellow/red from global event tokens.
9. **PassAccuracy** — small **black** `ink.mark` sparks; highest visual layer; scattered across the whole mark area (not only near grid).

**Do not** use random rotation on shots/corners/offsides. Use 0°, 90°, or 180° only.

---

## PossessionGrid placement

| Side | Anchor | Token sizing |
|------|--------|--------------|
| Home (MEX) | **Top-left** of team zone | `gridSize` 604px, `circleSize` 60px at 1920×1080 via `resolvePossessionGridMetrics()` |
| Away (KOR) | **Top-right** of team zone (grid flush to outer edge) | Same tokens, mirrored |

- Filled circles = `c1`; empty = `paper.cream`
- Grid is a **square** footprint; do not stretch to fill the whole zone
- Grid occupies only `gridRegion`; marks use `markRegion` below (+ full width beside grid)

---

## Event mark placement (markRegion)

Target behavior from the reference:

| Parameter | Target | Config key |
|-----------|--------|------------|
| Spread | Marks fill **full height** of markRegion — dense mid and lower zone, not piled at top | `placementRows`, `placementCols` |
| Overlap | **Heavy** intentional overlap (~20–28% bbox overlap OK) | `composition.maxOverlapRatio` ≈ **0.24** |
| Inner bias | Marks drift **toward center gap** (inner edge of each side) | `homeInnerBias` / `awayInnerBias` ≈ **0.38** |
| Scale variance | Goals largest; cards/smallest; shots medium | `markScale`, Figma min/max per component |
| Static | **No** frame vibration, breathing, pulse, shake, or rotation wobble | `animation.staticRender: true` |

Placement engine: `findPlacement()` in `markRegion` with light overlap — **not** `clusterPoint`, not global Y ratios.

PassAccuracy sparks: random positions across **entire markRegion** (not tied to events); count from `passAccuracy.cleanSparkCount` / `brokenSparkCount`; always `ink.mark`.

